 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "70eac3dd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Attention Dilution v2 — Qwen3 (8B default on 40GB; 14B on 80GB)\n",
    "\n",
    "A clean reimplementation of phases 1-5 against **Qwen3** (8B by default, 14B if you have an 80GB GPU) with:\n",
    "- Real AdvBench (harmful) + Alpaca (harmless) datasets, not inline prompts\n",
    "- 256/256 direction-train pool, disjoint 100-prompt sweep eval, 512/520 baseline pool\n",
    "- 3-site residual ablation (resid_pre / resid_mid / resid_post) per layer\n",
    "- Layer sweep -> best-layer pick -> matched-pool validation\n",
    "- Phase 2 attention dilution scaling (H1 + H2 + behavior)\n",
    "- Jailbreak-threshold extraction (smallest N where refusal collapses)\n",
    "- Phase 3 steering rescue grid + MMLU-mini capability sanity\n",
    "- Phase 4 capability cost of V_refusal (intact vs ablated MMLU vs N)\n",
    "- Phase 5 refusal across (intact/ablated) x (harmful/harmless) x N\n",
    "- **NEW: attribution maps** — per-head DLA onto V_refusal across the (setting x N) grid, plus per-source-token contribution\n",
    "\n",
    "All sweeps are OOM-tolerant per cell and resume from CSVs on kernel restart.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Memory budget on 40GB A100 (Qwen3-8B default):**\n",
    "- Weights ~16 GB, leaves ~23 GB for activations / KV cache / hooks.\n",
    "- `MAX_ATTN_N=2048` caps the attention-pattern hooks; H2 + behavior continue past that.\n",
    "- `N_LONG=2048` for Phase 6 attribution maps.\n",
    "- For an 80GB GPU: `MODEL_NAME='Qwen/Qwen3-14B'`, `N_CTX=18000`, `MAX_ATTN_N=4096`, `N_LONG=4096`.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
