    "df5 = pd.read_csv(OUT/\"phase5_refusal_2x2.csv\").sort_values([\"setting\",\"prompt_type\",\"N\"]).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "if \"status\" not in df5.columns: df5[\"status\"] = \"ok\"\n",
    "ok5 = df5[df5[\"status\"]==\"ok\"]; bad5 = df5[df5[\"status\"]!=\"ok\"]\n",
    "color_map = {\"intact\":\"#1f77b4\",\"ablated\":\"#d62728\"}\n",
    "dash_map  = {\"harmful\":\"solid\",\"harmless\":\"dash\"}\n",
    "fig = go.Figure()\n",
    "for setting in sorted(ok5[\"setting\"].unique()):\n",
    "    for prompt_type in sorted(ok5[\"prompt_type\"].unique()):\n",
    "        sub = ok5[(ok5[\"setting\"]==setting) & (ok5[\"prompt_type\"]==prompt_type)].sort_values(\"N\")\n",
    "        if len(sub)==0: continue\n",
    "        x = sub[\"N\"].replace(0,1).tolist()\n",
    "        fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=x, y=sub[\"refusal_rate\"],\n",
    "                                 name=f\"{setting}/{prompt_type}\", mode=\"lines+markers\",\n",
    "                                 line=dict(color=color_map.get(setting),\n",
    "                                           dash=dash_map.get(prompt_type,\"solid\"))))\n",
    "fig.update_layout(\n",
    "    title=f\"Phase 5: refusal across (setting, prompt_type) x N ({MODEL_SLUG})\",\n",
    "    xaxis=dict(title=\"N (log)\", type=\"log\"),\n",
    "    yaxis=dict(title=\"Refusal rate\", range=[-0.08,1.05]),\n",
    "    legend=dict(orientation=\"h\", y=-0.25), width=1000, height=560,\n",
    ")\n",
    "fig.write_image(str(OUT/\"fig_phase5_refusal_2x2.png\"), width=1000, height=560)\n",
    "fig.show()\n",
    "# Killer comparison\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    pivot = ok5.set_index([\"setting\",\"prompt_type\",\"N\"])[\"refusal_rate\"]\n",
    "    nmax = int(ok5[(ok5[\"setting\"]==\"intact\")&(ok5[\"prompt_type\"]==\"harmful\")][\"N\"].max())\n",
    "    a = pivot.loc[(\"intact\",\"harmful\",nmax)]\n",
    "    b = pivot.loc[(\"ablated\",\"harmful\",0)]\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nKiller comparison: intact/harmful @N={nmax}={a:.2%}  vs  ablated/harmful @N=0={b:.2%}\")\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(\"killer comparison unavailable:\", e)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b33d273a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Phase 6 — Attribution maps: where is V_refusal being written, and from where?\n",
    "\n",
    "A simple, faithful \"attribution graph\" we can compute on Qwen3-14B:\n",
    "\n",
    "For each cell of the (setting x N) grid we measure two things at the **last token** of the prompt:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Per-(layer, head) DLA onto V_refusal**: how much each head's write to the residual stream pushes the model toward refusal. This is a `[n_layers, n_heads]` heatmap.\n",
    "2. **Per-source-token contribution to the top guardrail head**: for the strongest guardrail head, the product `attn_pattern[last, src] * (||OV @ value[src]|| projected onto V_refusal)`, summed over the harmful span vs the bloat. This tells us *where the head is reading from*.\n",
    "\n",
    "Comparing these maps across (intact at N=0, intact at N=4096, ablated at N=0, ablated at N=4096) gives a single picture of:\n",
    "- which heads turn off when bloat grows (top dilution story)\n",
    "- which heads stay on when V_refusal is ablated (any \"redundant\" refusal heads we missed)\n",
    "- where the guardrail head reads from at long context (the harmful span vs the bloat)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 36,
   "id": "7e63bfd9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
